00:30:59,887 --> 00:31:02,117
It was kinda embarrassing, though.

410
00:31:02,167 --> 00:31:05,000
I had a feeling people were staring at us.

411
00:31:05,047 --> 00:31:07,242
- Nonsense.
- No. Here.

412
00:31:14,327 --> 00:31:17,364
I'm gonna carry you over the threshold.

413
00:31:34,767 --> 00:31:37,076
# Here comes the bride

414
00:31:37,127 --> 00:31:39,595
# All dressed in white

415
00:31:39,647 --> 00:31:44,357
# And there's the groom
standing right by her side #

416
00:31:44,407 --> 00:31:46,557
Everybody, this is Helen.

417
00:31:46,607 --> 00:31:49,360
Ben! This is the fella
that gave me my first job.

418
00:31:49,407 --> 00:31:52,365
This is Helen.
You remember Gene Krupa from the show.

419
00:31:52,407 --> 00:31:55,126
Here's Babe Russin, the tenor saxophone.

420
00:31:55,167 --> 00:31:57,761
You remember Chummy.
There's Polly and Don.

421
00:31:57,807 --> 00:32:00,241
We decided to celebrate.
We're gonna have a party.

422
00:32:00,287 --> 00:32:02,755
- Here?
- No, Harlem. Connie's Inn.

423
00:32:02,807 --> 00:32:04,684
Oh. Well, that's awful nice of you.

424
00:32:04,727 --> 00:32:08,003
Helen just arrived.
We've had the wedding and the show

425
00:32:08,047 --> 00:32:10,436
- and Helen's a little tired.
- I'm not.

426
00:32:10,487 --> 00:32:12,603
You've been on the train for three days.

427
00:32:12,647 --> 00:32:16,686
If your friends are nice enough
to give us a party, we should go!

428
00:32:16,727 --> 00:32:19,878
- Wonderful!
- We've already got reservations.

