00:33:16,927 --> 00:33:18,724
# Is the street

432
00:33:19,727 --> 00:33:22,764
# Where the folks really meet... #

433
00:33:22,807 --> 00:33:24,525
Who's he?

434
00:33:24,567 --> 00:33:26,922
Who? Louis Armstrong!

435
00:33:32,847 --> 00:33:37,921
# Yeah, yeah, yeah, really, yeah

436
00:33:37,967 --> 00:33:41,846
# Yeah, this is a treat

437
00:33:41,887 --> 00:33:47,280
# A-swingin' on Basin Street, yeah #

438
00:33:55,487 --> 00:33:57,364
Hey, Gene! Gene Krupa there!

439
00:33:57,407 --> 00:34:00,285
What'd you say?
Come here, man. Gimme some skin.

440
00:34:00,327 --> 00:34:03,319
- How you doin'?
- Won't you join us?

441
00:34:03,367 --> 00:34:06,518
Babe Russin! Don't you wanna swing
with the boys?

442
00:34:11,207 --> 00:34:13,198
- Is that gin?
- Yeah.

443
00:34:30,807 --> 00:34:32,798
(Drowned out by drum solo)

444
00:35:40,167 --> 00:35:43,921
Glenn, come here, daddy.
Beat out one like you did with Ben Pollack.

445
00:35:43,967 --> 00:35:45,605
Be right back.

446
00:37:16,607 --> 00:37:19,246
(Cheering and whistling)

447
00:37:21,847 --> 00:37:23,758
(# Blues piano)

448
00:37:33,607 --> 00:37:36,485
- Nice goin', Glenn.
- You were wonderful!

449
00:37:36,527 --> 00:37:39,280
It's fun but I don't kid myself.

450
00:37:39,327 --> 00:37:42,205
When I start playing jazz
with Louis Armstrong and Gene Krupa,

451
00:37:42,247 --> 00:37:45,205
I'm lucky if I come in third, isn't that right?

452
00:37:45,247 --> 00:37:48,080
- Where have you been, Mr Miller?
- Dr Schillinger!

453
00:37:48,127 --> 00:37:52,040
- It must be over a year.
- Glad to see you. This is my wife.

454
00:37:52,087 --> 00:37:54,999
- Very pleased to meet you.
- You remember Chummy.

455
00:37:55,047 --> 00:37:59,120
I missed you but I can see
you had a very charming distraction.

456
00:37:59,167 --> 00:38:01,840
Yeah, well, glad to see you, Doctor.

457
00:38:01,887 --> 00:38:05,436
- Who's Dr Schillinger? Were you sick?
- No, he's a musician.

458
00:38:05,487 --> 00:38:08,843
He worked out a new method
of composition. I studied with him.

459
00:38:08,887 --> 00:38:12,675
- Why did you stop?
- I got busy and it was expensive.

460
00:38:12,727 --> 00:38:14,763
Want something else to eat?

461
00:38:15,767 --> 00:38:19,555
- Maybe we'd better call it a day.
- No, I'm having a...

462
00:38:19,607 --> 00:38:22,758
- No, I really had a wonderful time.
- Yes, dear.

463
00:38:22,807 --> 00:38:25,082
- Bye.
- Good night.

